@Max P 
Not exactly true. The pyramids were built as tombs and remains have been found in some of them. The better preserved tombs are ones that aren't conspicuous (like a pyramid).

No mummies have been found in the pyramids of Giza. They have burial chambers but are otherwise empty. It is not certain if they were never used or (more likely) looted in ancient times.
